The paper deals with domain adaptation in visual recognition and prediction settings, specifically in digit classification and semantic segmentation of road scenes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also uses adversarial training and cycle-consistency constraints, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as semantic segmentation, which falls under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image and video processing, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
